summary: For you Marvel fans, I recommend James Young’s episode of the JAMcast podcast. For those that don’t know James, he coordinated...
body:
For you Marvel fans, I recommend James Young’s episode of the JAMcast podcast. For those that don’t know James, he coordinated the fights for Winter Soldier, Civil War, Infinity War and Endgame. He also doubled for Bucky and Iron Man. It’s a super fascinating listen to what goes on behind the scenes in Marvel films.

For example, he talks about how the stunt double for Chadwick Boseman had to wear seven layers of costume for Blank Panther. Since he was fighting in a hundred degree weather, he was shooting a scene, violently throwing up in a bucket, chugging a Powerade then moving onto the next scene. That’s dedication.

He also talks about how Chris Evans has a semi-photographic memory for choreography. He can watch a fight twice and then know exactly how it goes. It’s a proper interesting chat and the guy is super genuine. Well worth a listen. Search for JAMcast on Apple podcasts and you’ll find it.

title: Judas is a Woman
body:
Iron Man #173

Tony has lost his company.

  • Again, the drama of Tony’s self-destruction gives us the best scenes.
  • Jim’s mission involves rescuing the woman who started Tony on his decline. Except she’s not really a hostage. Really, it’s frustratingly vague what’s going on here. And how close her ties are to the real villain.
  • We do learn more about her. And the script tries to justify why exactly Tony fell so hard and fast for her. It’s not really convincing but you have to give some credit for the effort to improve the early part of this story arc.
  • Denny O'Neil (15 of 49).
  • Luke McDonnell (12 of 37). 

7/10

title: Firebrand's Revenge
body:
Iron Man #172

Pretty solid drama, as Captain America tries to get Tony to sober up.

  • The Coincidence Factor: An old villain of Iron Man sees them and decides to attack. But, random coincidence or not, it actually works pretty well and adds to the story without dominating it.
  • Watching Tony’s team contemplate unemployment really drives home the seriousness of what’s happening here.
  • Denny O'Neil (14 of 49).
  • Luke McDonnell (11 of 37). 

9/10
